DPP Keriako Tobiko has directed the DCI to investigate the chaos that left several wounded in Migori on Monday."You have been directed to immediately and urgently commence investigations into the incident," Tobiko said in a statement."...and submit the resultant file for perusal and directions," he said on Tuesday in a letter to DCI Ndegwa Muhoro.Mombasa Governor Hassan Joho's bodyguard was shot and injured during the ODM rally at Posta grounds.The rally was completely disrupted when Migori governor Okoth Obado arrived unannounced when Kisumu Senator Anyang&rsquo; Nyong&rsquo;o was addressing the crowd.Immediately after seeing him, the crowd booed and threw water bottles, stones and shoes at the podium.This forced Obado's guards to fire in the air. A bullet went through a VIP seat in an area where dignitaries were seated.Joho's bodyguard was shot during the fracas.Mvita MP Abdulswamad Nassir said: "This was an assassination attempt. They were after Joho. Our car was shot at three times."More on this: Joho bodyguard shot during chaotic ODM rally in MigoriAlso read: Migori attack 'an assassination attempt' by trained security officers - Joho